Project Topics to Be Included
Each student project must include the following topics and functionalities:
1. Project Setup
• Initialize a Node.js project
• Install and configure required dependencies
• Organize the project using a clean folder structure (routes, controllers, models,
middleware)
2. Server Creation
• Create an Express server
• Configure middleware (JSON parsing, error handling)
• Use environment variables for configuration
3. Database Connection
• Connect the application to MongoDB
• Use Mongoose for database interaction
• Handle database connection errors
4. Application Routing
• Create RESTful API routes
• Use proper HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT/PATCH, DELETE)
• Structure routes based on resources (users, main entities)
5. User Authentication
• Implement user registration
• Implement user login
• Hash passwords using bcrypt
• Generate authentication tokens using JSON Web Token (JWT)
6. User Authorization
• Protect private routes using JWT middleware
• Allow users to access only their own data
• Implement role-based access if needed (optional)
7. Data Modeling
• Create database schemas using Mongoose
• Define relationships between collections
• Use required fields and default values
8. Data Validation
• Validate request data on the server side
• Prevent invalid or empty data from being saved
• Return meaningful validation error messages
9. CRUD Operations
• Create new records (POST)
• Read data (GET all / GET by ID)
• Update existing records (PUT / PATCH)
• Delete records (DELETE)
10. Profile or Main Entity Management
• Create a main profile or core entity related to the project
• Allow users to create and update their own profile or main data
• Link the profile/entity to the authenticated user
11. Data Ownership & Security
• Ensure users can access only their own resources
• Prevent unauthorized access or modification
• Handle forbidden actions correctly
14. Error Handling
• Handle application and database errors
• Use consistent error response structure
• Avoid application crashes due to unhandled errors
15. API Testing
• Test endpoints using Postman or similar tools
• Verify authentication and authorization flow
• Validate CRUD functionality